issue.title: Bump electron from 26.2.0 to 27.0.4

labels.name: dependencies
labels.description: Pull requests that update a dependency file

issue.body:
Bumps [electron](https://github.com/electron/electron) from 26.2.0 to 27.0.4.
Release notes

Sourced from electron's releases.

electron v27.0.4

Release Notes for v27.0.4

Fixes

  • Fixed an issue where WebViews could sometimes crash on unload. #40444 (Also in 26, 28)
  • Fixed rendering on Linux due to broken shader cache compilation with driver updates. #40467

Other Changes

  • Updated Chromium to 118.0.5993.129. #40417

electron v27.0.3

Release Notes for v27.0.3

Fixes

  • Fixed an error changing file format in dialog.showOpenDialog on macOS. #40347 (Also in 28)
  • Fixed an issue where navigator.keyboard.lock() did not work per latest expected behavior. #40388 (Also in 26, 28)

Other Changes

  • Updated Chromium to 118.0.5993.120. #40404

electron v27.0.2

Release Notes for v27.0.2

Fixes

  • Functions called over the contextBridge are now called with the expected receiver (this). #40262 (Also in 28)

Other Changes

  • Backported fix for 1473422. #40280

electron v27.0.1

Release Notes for v27.0.1

Fixes

  • Fixed an issue where Windows Toast notifications weren't properly dismissed from the Action Center on notification.close() if they'd previously been dismissed. #40244 (Also in 26, 28)
  • Fixed an issue where calling loadURL during some webContents url loading events could crash. #40162 (Also in 24, 25, 26)
  • Fixed an issue where fully occluded windows would return an empty image from webContents.capturePage() on Windows and Linux. #40188 (Also in 25, 26, 28)
  • Fixed an issue with webContents interaction with fullscreen and WCO on macOS. #40217 (Also in 25, 26, 28)
  • Fixed some redundant permission dialogs while screen sharing on Wayland. #40193 (Also in 26, 28)

Other Changes

  • Updated Chromium to 118.0.5993.89. #40240

electron v27.0.0

Release Notes for v27.0.0

Stack Upgrades

... (truncated)

Commits
  • 206364d fix: broken shader cache due to compilation error (#40467)
  • f9702ca docs: fix hid-device-{added|removed|revoked} event types (#40477)
  • 3148a2a fix: crash when unloading some WebViews (#40444)
  • 272b371 chore: bump chromium to 118.0.5993.129 (27-x-y) (#40417)
  • bbc12f6 docs: add bypassCustomProtocolHandlers to ses.fetch (#40423)
  • a6a35f1 docs: document our Node.js versioning policy (#40415)
  • 0beed97 chore: bump chromium to 118.0.5993.120 (27-x-y) (#40404)
  • a22f611 build: actually show github upload output if verbose is true. (#40399)
  • 4487ff5 fix: navigator.keyboard.lock() fullscreen exit handling (#40388)
  • 6b87170 chore: bump chromium to 118.0.5993.119 (27-x-y) (#40355)
  • Additional commits viewable in compare view

issue.title: Add theory agnostic analysis with POI as NOI to CI
issue.body:
Testing if it works. For the histogram it reuses the same file as for the traditional analysis, which is augmented with the yieldsTheoryAgnostic histogram. Then the setupCombine and fit parts are simply duplicated from the standard wmass workflow.

No change should be expected for the traditional analysis in the impacts and other plots. A new plot is added for the impact from the theory agnostic fit (but it is possible the fit doesn't even converge when using a small fraction of the MC stat, to be seen).

comment.body:
This is a plot I got from a test local run with 1:1 data/MC stat: https://mciprian.web.cern.ch/mciprian/WMassAnalysis/fromMyWremnants/fitResults/theoryAgnostic_poiAsNoi/09Nov2023/WMass_eta_pt_charge/makeImpactsOnMW/impactsOnMw_compare_noQCDtheorySyst.pdf

It compares the impacts with and without PDF/QCD theory systs. It was mainly to see if the numbers are still compatible with what we used to get before (note that here I used a random |yW|/ptW binning, 5 uniform bins each from 0 to 2.5 and 0 to 50 GeV, so it's not the same default binning as the code, which uses the optimised one from Elisabetta).

Unless there are counter objections, I'll update the PR to automatically remove PDFs and QCD uncertainties for the theory agnostic, and fix CI to make the proper impact plot
